{
  "doc_id": "25953",
  "text": "The pJNRM and pKCcas9-metK vectors were then transferred into S. pogona through protoplast transformation by employing a previously published method [CITATION_1] , respectively. Apramycin (50 µg/mL) was used to select transformants. The transformants named SPOG-RM and SPOG-ME were confirmed by PCR using primers for the apramycin resistance gene ( Supplementary Table 1 ).",
